OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784913524
OL,3,CCumbria Tourism says business rates
OL,4,Ccut is not enough
OL,6,FPrime Minister Andy Burnham has
OL,7,Fdescribed his latest move as
OL,8,Fprotecting "the beating heart of our
OL,9,Fcommunities": pubs and local high
OL,10,Fstreets.
OL,12,FPubs, clubs and live music venues in
OL,13,FEngland will receive a 20% cut to
OL,14,Ftheir business rates from next April,
OL,15,Fwhich the Government says will save
OL,16,Fthe typical pub an estimated #1,100
OL,17,Fnext year.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G1/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784913524
OL,3,CCumbria Tourism says business rates
OL,4,Ccut is not enough
OL,6,FBut in Cumbria, where tourism supports
OL,7,F28% of the county's workforce, the
OL,8,Fbody representing the hospitality
OL,9,Findustry says the change is welcome
OL,10,Fbut does not go far enough.
OL,12,FGill Haigh, Managing Director of
OL,13,FCumbria Tourism, said any measure
OL,14,Feasing pressure is welcome because
OL,15,F"These businesses play a vital role in
OL,16,FCumbria's communities and visitor
OL,17,Feconomy, and many are still facing
OL,18,Fsignificant cost pressures."
OL,26,@wD@AOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784913524
OL,3,CCumbria Tourism says business rates
OL,4,Ccut is not enough
OL,6,FThe organisation still feels that
OL,7,Fburden of "rising costs, staffing
OL,8,Fpressures and squeezed margins" is not
OL,9,Fentirely recognised by this move.
OL,11,FCumbria Tourism backs UKHospitality's
OL,12,F_VATsTheProblem campaign, which is
OL,13,Fcalling for VAT on hospitality
OL,14,Fbusinesses to be reduced to 10%.
OL,16,FGill Haigh continues, "A broader VAT
OL,17,Freduction would give more meaningful
OL,18,Fsupport across the sector, helping
OL,19,Fbusinesses protect jobs, invest, and
OL,20,Fremain competitive."
OL,26,@xD@WOU|D@TO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784913524
OL,3,CCumbria Tourism says business rates
OL,4,Ccut is not enough
OL,6,FThe Government, however, says this is
OL,7,Fpart of a series of measures including
OL,8,Felectricity bill VAT relief and a #2
OL,9,Fbus fare cap it says are cutting costs
OL,10,Ffor working people.
OL,12,FPrime Minister Andy Burnham said, "For
OL,13,Ftoo long, governments have stood by
OL,14,Fwhile cherished venues have
OL,15,Fdisappeared from our local high
OL,16,Fstreets. So today I am changing that."
OL,26,@tD@cOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784913524
OL,3,CCumbria Tourism says business rates
OL,4,Ccut is not enough
OL,6,FHe says his government is backing "the
OL,7,Fbusinesses that people want to see in
OL,8,Ftheir communities." He says it is just
OL,9,Fthe start and promises "to bring back
OL,10,Fhope across the country."
OL,12,FChancellor of the Exchequer John
OL,13,FHealey added that the Government will
OL,14,F"give businesses the support they need
OL,15,Fand generate growth in every postcode."
OL,17,FBut across the hospitality sector and
OL,18,Fin the Lake District, businesses say
OL,19,Fthe support they need is a cut to VAT.
OL,26,@nD@cOUrD@YO]vD@AOUwD@gO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/6
